# FDA Establishment Registration and Device Listing

Produces a submission-ready registration and device listing package aligned to 21 CFR Part 807.

## Prerequisites

1. **Entity profile** — legal name, ownership structure, addresses, contacts, FEI (if assigned)
2. **Business activities** — manufacturer/contract manufacturer/specification developer/repackager/relabeller, etc.
3. **Responsible official** — name, title, authority to sign, contact details
4. **Device inventory** — product codes, device names, classification, regulation numbers, intended use
5. **Regulatory history** — prior listing numbers, 510(k)/PMA/De Novo references, exemptions with citations
6. **Foreign establishments** — U.S. agent details (name, address, email, phone)
7. **Source documents** — prior FDA submissions, labeling, IFUs, QMS scope, corporate records

## Output Structure / Process

**Process Checklist**
- Validate current FDA registration window, fees, and submission portal requirements (FURLS/DRLM). [VERIFY]
- Confirm product codes and classifications against FDA Product Classification database. [VERIFY]
- Verify all identifiers (FEI, listing numbers, premarket submission IDs) against source records.

**Document Structure**

| Section | Required Content |
| --- | --- |
| Header | Title, preparation date, regulatory basis (21 CFR Part 807), submission context (initial/annual/update) |
| Establishment Details | Legal owner name, FEI, physical/mailing address, phone/email, website, DUNS/identifier if used |
| Business Activities | FDA-recognized activity types, per-site activity mapping if multiple facilities |
| Owner/Operator | Responsible official(s), title, authority basis, contact info |
| Device Listing Summary | Total devices listed, device family/grouping logic, prior listing references |
| Compliance Statements | QSR applicability, exemption claims with citations, certification of accuracy |
| Foreign Establishment | U.S. agent details and acknowledgment (if applicable) |
| Signatures | Attestation language, signatory blocks, date |

**Device Listing Table Template**

| Device Name | Product Code | Regulation # | Class | Intended Use (1–2 lines) | Listing # (if any) | 510(k)/PMA/De Novo | Exemption Basis |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |

**Compliance/Attestation Language Template**

- Certify information is true and complete; acknowledge legal consequences of false statements.
- Confirm authority of signatory to bind establishment.
- Identify any exemptions and cite regulatory basis. [VERIFY]
- If foreign, confirm designation of U.S. agent and provide contact details.

## Guidelines

- Do not invent product codes, classifications, or regulatory IDs; mark unknowns as `TBD`.
- Intended use must align with labeling and premarket submissions; avoid new claims.
- If listing exemptions are claimed, cite the exact regulation and rationale. [VERIFY]
- Keep activity descriptions consistent with FDA-defined terminology.
- Use consistent entity naming across all sections; match corporate records.
- Flag any discrepancies between source documents and provided data for client confirmation.
